    {
      "heading_text": "Name resolution",
      "normalized_heading_text": "name resolution",
      "level": 2,
      "line_start": 848,
      "line_end": 853,
      "prose_text": "2. Name resolution precedes data flows. For each site, DNS queries precede\nconnection establishment. Cached domains reduce or eliminate network DNS lookups. Where DNS is slow or fails, application flows stall, a reminder that name resolution is on the critical path.",
      "full_text": "2. Name resolution precedes data flows. For each site, DNS queries precede\nconnection establishment. Cached domains reduce or eliminate network DNS lookups. Where DNS is slow or fails, application flows stall, a reminder that name resolution is on the critical path.",
      "word_count": 39,
      "empty": false,
      "asset_only": false
    },
    {
      "heading_text": "Latency, jitter, and",
      "normalized_heading_text": "latency jitter and",
      "level": 2,
      "line_start": 854,
      "line_end": 866,
      "prose_text": "3. Latency, jitter, and paths. Repeated 100-ping batches reveal that where the server is\n(and when you measure) matters: nearby U.S. hosts exhibit low median RTTs and tight dispersion, while overseas hosts have higher medians with larger tails. Traceroute highlights the longest link(s)-often a transoceanic or inter-regional backbone, and occasional path changes across runs.\nSYN,ACK->ACK is almost entirely host processing. ECN flags (ECE/CWR) may appear during handshake on networks that negotiate congestion-experienced signaling.\n5. Practical analysis aids. Custom columns for ports and HTTP fields, plus simple\ncoloring rules, significantly speed up triage-particularly when QUIC, DNS, and TLS traffic interleave. Protocol Hierarchy and “Follow TCP Stream” provide fast summaries and per-flow clarity, respectively.",
      "full_text": "3. Latency, jitter, and paths. Repeated 100-ping batches reveal that where the server is\n(and when you measure) matters: nearby U.S. hosts exhibit low median RTTs and tight dispersion, while overseas hosts have higher medians with larger tails. Traceroute highlights the longest link(s)-often a transoceanic or inter-regional backbone, and occasional path changes across runs.\nSYN,ACK->ACK is almost entirely host processing. ECN flags (ECE/CWR) may appear during handshake on networks that negotiate congestion-experienced signaling.\n5. Practical analysis aids. Custom columns for ports and HTTP fields, plus simple\ncoloring rules, significantly speed up triage-particularly when QUIC, DNS, and TLS traffic interleave. Protocol Hierarchy and “Follow TCP Stream” provide fast summaries and per-flow clarity, respectively.\n---",
